This directory contains the JavaScript source modules for the chess UI.
These modules are merged by build-chess.py / build-chess.sh into chess.html.

License classification by file:
  - game-logic.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      PGN disambiguation and SAN notation logic from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder(): prepends a null placeholder to
          moveRecords when a new game starts with Black to move (FEN/setup
          /PGN import paths). Syncs stateHistory[0].moveRecords so the
          placeholder survives undo back to the opening.
        - boardVersion integer on game state (incremented by makeMv /
          makeMvInPlace / _refreshStateAfterSetup, restored by unmakeMv,
          initialized to 1 by fenToState / initState) — used by the
          _updateBoardIncremental dirty check for ~100x faster render ticks.
        - moveAlg() disambiguation: replaced cloneB-per-candidate with
          makeMvInPlace/unmakeMv — eliminates up to 8 board clones per
          moveAlg call (e.g. 8 pawns that could capture on the same file).
        - pieceZobristIdx(): hoisted the {pawn:0,knight:1,...} type-index
          lookup to module scope (_PIECE_TYPE_IDX) instead of building a
          fresh object literal on every call (32+ calls per computeHash).
        - isDeadPosition(): single-pass 64-square scan with early returns
          (pawns/rooks/queens → not dead) instead of allocating a pcs[]
          array + multiple .filter()/.map() passes. Bishop square-color
          parity tracked inline. Same FIDE 5.2.2 coverage, ~3x faster.
  - ai-bridge.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      Engine communication patterns from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _buildPGNString() now appends `{score eval_word}` after every
          move with a cached eval in _reviewEvalCache, and
          `{SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}` every 5 moves (engine name,
          depth, score, WDL). Helper: _formatPGNEvalAnnotation().
        - exportPGNToFile() + onPGNExported() for SAF-based PGN export.
        - _fileBrowserSelect() no longer calls showToast() after
          bridge.importSettings() — the onSettingsImported callback is
          the single source of truth for the import result toast,
          eliminating the duplicate-toast bug.
        - _safeExecute() wrapper in Java side catches
          RejectedExecutionException from engineExecutor and notifies
          JS via onEngineError (see StockfishNative.java).
        - restartCurrentEngine() and onEngineRestarting() both clear
          _reviewEvalCache, _multiPVLines, _multiPVResult,
          _lastEngineVariation to prevent stale evals from the old
          engine instance.
        - Ponder-Hit fix: uses JS-side cached _lastPonderMoveFromEngine
          instead of re-calling Java getLastPonderMove() (which is a
          one-shot read).
        - PV variation cache + fork grafting: _pvCache (Map) +
          _convertPVtoSANCached() + _checkPVDivergence(). Caches the
          converted SAN + post-state for every UCI prefix encountered
          during a single _processDeferredVariations() call, keyed by
          (state.hash, uciPrefix). MultiPV lines sharing a common prefix
          (e.g. e4 e5 Nf3) now convert the prefix exactly once instead
          of N times. Cache is cleared per-search (bounded at 200 entries).
        - generateFEN(): hoisted the PIECE_FEN lookup table to module
          scope (_PIECE_FEN) instead of allocating a fresh
          {white:{...},black:{...}} object on every call. generateFEN
          is called on every AI move, hint, and eval request.
        - _esc() / _escJs(): single-pass regex with callback + lookup
          map instead of 5 chained .replace() calls (5 intermediate
          string allocations → 1). These helpers are called on every
          move notation, file path, and ECO name during render.
        - _formatPGNEvalAnnotation(): explicit parenthesization of the
          mate-detection condition + Number() coercion of cached
          mate/eval values (defensive against JSON string values).
  - ui.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      UI layout and interaction patterns from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - startGame() now auto-fills ECO opening moves into moveRecords
          with proper SAN notation as it replays each move — the user
          sees the full opening sequence from move #1, no "..."
          placeholder needed.
        - _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder() called at 4 new-game entry
          points (startGame, _applyImportedFEN, exitSetup, importPGN).
        - redoMove() no longer calls doAIMove() — the redo stack
          contains pre-recorded moves; triggering a fresh AI search
          would corrupt the stack.
        - "Play Again" button now shows ⚔️ prefix.
        - executeMove() setTimeout(420ms) callback captures
          gameState.hash before the timeout and aborts if it changes,
          preventing stale callbacks from overwriting new state during
          undo/redo/flip (the "ghost game-over banner" bug).
        - doAIMove() moved out of the rAF callback into setTimeout(0)
          so the browser can paint the post-move UI before the engine
          starts thinking.
        - toggleSetup() simplified — removed dead 'play' status check.
        - infoCtrl now references the control-map entry directly
          instead of allocating a fresh {white,black} object per render.
        - _cachedBwrap liveness check changed from parentNode to
          document.body.contains() for stricter validation.
        - _updateSingleSq(): signature-based dirty check — builds a
          cheap signature string (piece + selection + last-move +
          check + legal + control-map + anim) and skips all DOM writes
          (style.background, className, innerHTML) when the signature
          hasn't changed. Previously rebuilt innerHTML for all 64
          squares on every engine-progress callback (~10-50/sec).
        - _getSqBg(): removed unused _sqBgCache declaration + dead
          lastFrom/lastTo computation (variables were computed but
          never used in the return value).
  - tablebase.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      PGN parsing logic (GameTree/PgnToken/PgnScanner) from DroidFish.
      Copyright (C) Peter Österlund. Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _applyImportedFEN() and importPGN() call
          _prependBlackToMovePlaceholder() when the imported position
          has Black to move.
        - PGN variation continuation loop changed from `break` (truncate
          entire variation on first unparseable token) to `continue`
          (skip only that token, keep parsing the rest). moveAlg-based
          forgiving fallback applied uniformly to every token.
        - When an unparseable token is skipped, the side-to-move and
          move number now advance — a skipped move still consumes a
          turn per PGN spec, otherwise the next token would be
          attributed to the wrong side, desynchronizing the variation.
        - _tbCache (tablebase LRU cache) now refreshes on hit (delete +
          set) so frequently-accessed entries don't get evicted before
          cold entries. Previously only `get` was called without
          reordering, defeating LRU semantics.
  - ai-bridge.js: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      v1.0.2 additional fixes (second-pass review):
        - _formatVariationGroups(): variation line numbers are now assigned
          SEQUENTIALLY (1, 2, 3, ...) based on array position, not derived
          from group/mpvIndex/lineNum fields. The old scheme could collide
          (mainline=1, mpvIndex=0 also=1) producing duplicate "🌿线1"
          labels when both were attached to the same move (common after
          Flip or when multiple MultiPV lines diverge at the same move).
        - _checkPVDivergenceSANs(): added same-SAN dedup guard to prevent
          the same variation from being attached multiple times.
        - _mrToUci(): knight promotion letter 'k' → 'n' (UCI spec). Was
          causing false PV divergence for every knight promotion.
        - _resetGameUIState() in ui.js now resets isAIThinking,
          _aiSafetyTimerId, _aiRetryCount, _evalLoading, _sfEvalReady,
          _ponderGen, _ponderMoveSAN, _ponderBarInfo, _pendingPonderMoveUCI,
          _multiPVLines, _multiPVResult, _lastEngineVariation — prevents
          stale AI state from leaking into a new game (was causing "AI
          never moves" if the user started a new game during AI thinking).
        - onBestMove(): removed the `moveRecords.length > 0` guard so
          variations are tracked even when the AI plays the first move
          (player plays Black). Was causing no 🌿 variation lines for
          the AI's first move when playing Black.
        - _aiRetryCount reset added to onEngineReady() and
          onEngineRestarting() — prevents the retry counter from
          carrying over after a crash-recovery, which could immediately
          hit the 3-retry cap and show "AI timeout" despite the engine
          just having recovered.
        - onStatsRequestReview(): shows a toast when moveRecords is empty
          instead of silently returning.
        - _reviewEvalCache gains a peek() method (read without LRU
          refresh); iteration loops in _buildEvalTrendSVG,
          _findCriticalMoves, move-list render, and openStatsPage use
          peek() to avoid churning the Map.
        - openStatsPage() now also sends moveRecords (from/to/piece/
          captured/promotion/notation) in the payload — the stats page
          uses them to replay moves correctly instead of re-parsing the
          PGN string with its simplified parser (which cascade-failed
          on complex moves, capping the total move count).
        - Removed dead _checkPVDivergence(pv1, pv2) function (shadowed
          by the no-arg _checkPVDivergence() that iterates
          _pendingEnginePVs — JS last-declaration-wins rule made the
          former unreachable).
        - Removed onStatsRequestImport() and its export (stats import
          now stays inside StatsActivity).
        - executeMove() ponder-hit check: promotion piece name → UCI
          letter (queen→'q' etc.) so promotion moves can match the
          engine's UCI ponder move (was always failing, defeating
          ponder for all promotions).
        - makeMv() in game-logic.js: reuse capPiece for Zobrist hash
          instead of re-reading from original state (redundant read).
        - v1.0.2 (qw3.7max audit) — 7 optimizations from the external
          code-review report, all implemented:
          (1) _updateBoardLightweight(): state-comparison logic (_selChanged,
              _newHover→_infoChanged) rewritten with optional chaining (?.)
              for cleaner null-safe comparison; renamed _newHover to
              _infoChanged (the variable tracks info-square changes, not
              just hover).
          (2) Review move-classification span: _mcls.color and _mcls.label
              now wrapped in _esc() for defensive XSS protection (currently
              redundant since _classifyMove returns internal constants, but
              guards against future changes).
          (3) scrollIntoView behavior:'instant' → 'auto' at 2 call sites
              (review-mode auto-scroll) for broader compatibility with
              older WebView engines that don't support the CSSOM View
              'instant' value.
          (4) Review auto-scroll: rAF+setTimeout(0) → double rAF. The first
              rAF fires after layout, the second after paint — reading
              layout info (scrollIntoView) in the second rAF guarantees no
              forced synchronous layout (layout thrashing). The old
              rAF+setTimeout(0) pattern couldn't guarantee layout was
              complete because setTimeout is a macrotask that may run
              before the browser's layout/paint step.
          (5) _sqElCache: 2D array-of-arrays → 1D array indexed by (r*8+c).
              Single contiguous allocation, no nested array objects, one
              fewer pointer dereference per access. With 10-50 engine
              progress callbacks/sec, this shaves a small but measurable
              amount off the hot incremental-update path.
          (6) _isMoverWhite: ((i+1)%2)===1 → (i%2)===0 (mathematically
              equivalent, eliminates the unnecessary +1). Applied at 2
              sites in ui.js (review move-list render + _findCriticalMoves).
          (7) _rListEl: module-level cache of the review-moves-list element,
              avoids getElementById('reviewMovesList') on every render's
              scroll-into-view path. Assigned after full render, cleared on
              cache invalidation.
          (8) Review move-classification span: string concatenation (+=)
              → ES6 template literal for readability (the span is built
              once per reviewed move, not in a hot loop).
  - eco-data.js: AGPL v3 (original)
      ECO opening data from lichess-org/chess-openings (CC0).
      Code is original — not derived from DroidFish.
  - index.html.tpl: AGPL v3 (original CSS/HTML template)
  - build-chess.sh / build-chess.py: AGPL v3 (original build scripts)

v1.0.2 stats.html updates (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived PGN parsing):
  - parsePGN() now checks for _payload.moveRecords (sent by the main
    app). If present, calls parseFromMoveRecords() to replay the
    authoritative move list via executeMove() — avoids the simplified
    SAN parser's cascade-failure bug that capped total moves at ~98.
  - parseFromMoveRecords(): converts algebraic strings ("e2") to
    {row, col} objects (the main app stores from/to as strings; stats
    executeMove expects objects). Skips null placeholders.
  - renderPGNText() / renderSAN(): piece symbols now wrapped in their
    own <span class="piece-white/piece-black"> with the same
    color/stroke/glow as the main board. CSS specificity increased
    (.pgn-display .move .piece-white) so the piece color overrides
    .pgn-display .move. Previously the piece symbols were
    cream-colored (same as the rest of the move text) because
    .pgn-display .move (specificity 0,2,0) overrode .piece-white
    (specificity 0,1,0).
  - PGN import (📂 Select PGN File) now opens SAF picker directly
    from StatsActivity via statsSelectPGNFile() bridge method.
    onStatsPGNFileRead(content) callback updates the payload in place.
  - _statsPastePGN() no longer checks AndroidBridge.statsRequestImport
    (removed orphaned feature check).

v1.0.3 changes (in stats.html and chess.src/*.js):
  - ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNComment() format uses a single space as
    separator between thinking time and eval annotation.
    Examples: "{3.2s +0.5 略优}", "{3.2s SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}",
    "{3.2s}", "{+0.5 略优}" (eval only — no separator). Backward
    compatible with the earlier em-dash format on the parsing side.
  - game-logic.js: loading_title and built_in_only strings updated
    from v1.0.2 → v1.0.3.
  - ui.js: version badge (<span class="ver">v1.0.3</span>), about
    dialog (v1.0.3), and render-error fallback page (v1.0.3) updated.
  - index.html.tpl: <title>Regalia v1.0.3</title>.
  - stats.html (NOT in chess.src/, lives in assets/ directly):
      * stateToFEN(state): NEW — generates a FEN string from a game
        state (board placement, side to move, castling, en passant,
        halfmove clock, fullmove number).
      * extractMoveTimes(pgnText): NEW — extracts per-move thinking
        times from PGN comments in the {<sec>s ...} (v1.0.3),
        {<sec>s——...} (earlier em-dash format, back-compat), and [%clk HH:MM:SS]
        formats. Returns {usedTimes, clkTimes} arrays indexed by
        mainline move index.
      * formatTime(sec): NEW — human-readable time formatting
        (e.g. "12.3s", "3m 25s", "1h 12m 30s").
      * renderTimeChart(times): NEW — SVG bar chart of per-move
        thinking time. White moves = white bars, Black = blue bars.
      * renderFENPanel(effectiveParsed, selectedIdx): NEW — FEN
        display panel below the PGN text panel. Shows the FEN of the
        position after the selected move (mainline or variation),
        auto-generated from the post-state. Includes a copy-to-clipboard
        button (uses navigator.clipboard with execCommand fallback).
      * selectVariationMove(varId, varClickedIdx): NEW — handles
        variation-move clicks. Builds a synthetic move sequence:
        mainline[0..mainIdxBefore-1] + variation moves[0..varClickedIdx],
        where mainIdxBefore is the index of the mainline move that the
        variation's first move REPLACES. The synthetic sequence is used
        for ALL stats computation, giving per-position statistics for
        variation lines.
      * _variations[] array: NEW — registered by renderPGNText() as it
        walks the PGN. Each entry has {mainIdxBefore, moves:[SAN],
        sideAtStart}. Used by selectVariationMove() to reconstruct the
        synthetic sequence.
      * _variationMoves / _variationMeta: NEW state variables holding
        the current variation selection (mutually exclusive with
        _selectedMoveIdx for mainline selection).
      * renderStats() Time Management section: REPLACED the v1.0.2
        placeholder (which only counted [%clk] comments) with a
        comprehensive analysis: total/White/Black time, avg per move,
        slowest/fastest move, volatility (stddev), long-think count,
        quick-move count, phase distribution (opening/midgame/endgame),
        per-move time bar chart.
      * render() function: now resets _variations before each render,
        computes effectiveParsed (mainline slice, variation synthetic,
        or full), adds a selection banner above the PGN text panel,
        and inserts the FEN panel between PGN text and stats.
      * Bilingual UI strings: 30+ new i18n keys added (fen_label,
        fen_hint, fen_copy, time_*, variation_marker, select_hint,
        select_var_hint, etc.) for the existing ↔️ Chinese/English
        language toggle.
      * CSS: new .fen-panel, .time-chart-bar styles; responsive
        @media tweaks for small screens.

v1.0.3 patch changes (in addition to the v1.0.3 baseline above):
  - tablebase.js (GPL v3):
      * importPGN() variation post-process: Type A vs Type B distinction.
        The relocate loop now skips Type A variations (alternatives to the
        owning move — firstMoveIsWhite matches (mi%2===0)) so they remain
        attached to the owning move with correct move numbers. Previously
        Type A variations were incorrectly relocated to mi+1 and mislabeled
        as Type B continuations, producing nonsensical displays like
        "7... hxg3 Qxh1 8.Nc3 ..." for a variation that should be
        "7. hxg3 Qxh1 8.Nc3 ..." (White's alternative to 7.Kf2). This
        was the root cause of app-exported PGNs with variations failing
        to round-trip on re-import.
      * importPGN() and _applyImportedFEN(): set the new global
        _importedStartMoveNum from the FEN's fullMoveNumber so the move
        list, review mode, and PGN export display correct move numbers
        (e.g. "4. Bxf7+ Kxf7 5. Ne5" for a FEN starting at move 4,
        instead of "1. Bxf7+ Kxf7 2. Ne5").
      * _parsePGN() Phase 4 (cascade-failure fix): when a main-line token
        fails to parse, push a "skipped" placeholder entry (with
        skipped:true + skippedSAN) so moveRecords indices stay aligned
        with PGN move numbers, AND advance the side-to-move (bump
        fullMoveNumber if black was to move) so subsequent tokens have a
        chance to parse. Previously, a single invalid token would leave
        the side-to-move unchanged, causing EVERY subsequent token to
        also fail (wrong side's move) — manifesting as "only the first N
        moves import, the rest are silently dropped". Safety cap: 5
        consecutive skips stops the parse. Symptom was: app-exported
        PGNs with one illegal move imported only the prefix up to that
        move; now all OTHER moves import with a single "—" marker where
        the illegal move was.
      * importPGN() replay loop: handle "skipped" placeholder moves by
        pushing a null moveRecord (same as the black-to-move placeholder)
        so the display layer renders a dimmed "..." marker, keeping
        moveRecords indices aligned with PGN move numbers.
  - ai-bridge.js (GPL v3):
      * _buildPGNString(): uses _importedStartMoveNum as the move-pair
        number offset so PGN exports from a FEN-started game preserve the
        original move numbers from the FEN header.
      * New global _importedStartMoveNum (default 1) tracks the starting
        move number for PGN/FEN imports. Reset to 1 by startGame() and
        exitSetup() in ui.js.
  - ui.js (GPL v3):
      * Move history list (main mode + review mode): move-pair numbers
        now use _importedStartMoveNum as the offset. Click-to-review
        onclick handlers now use the moveRecords index `i` (stored in
        pair.wi / pair.bi) instead of computing reviewStep from pr.n,
        so the reviewStep is correct regardless of the FEN offset.
      * _exitSetupImpl() and _startGameImpl(): reset/set
        _importedStartMoveNum to track the starting move number for
        setup-mode positions and to reset to 1 for fresh games.
      * Landscape review mode: COMPLETE REDESIGN. The old layout put
        board + chart + controls all in .review-left (left column) with
        the move list in .review-moves (right column). The new layout
        splits into .review-top (board + moves, side by side) and
        .review-bottom (chart + slider + eval + nav + analyze, full
        width edge-to-edge). The whole .review-body scrolls vertically
        when content overflows. Key changes:
        - Chart now spans FULL viewport width (edge-to-edge, no gaps)
          instead of being squeezed under the board.
        - Chart height is ~35% of viewport height (generous).
        - Move list width is capped at 90% of board width (always
          narrower than the board, per user requirement).
        - Nav buttons (⏮ ◀ ▶ ⏭) are wrapped in .review-nav with
          flex:1 1 0 on each button so they stretch horizontally to
          fill the full width.
        - Board sizing: 60% of viewport height for the board+moves row,
          65% of viewport width for the board (leaving 35% for moves).
      * Portrait review mode: unchanged (original stacked layout).
      * v1.0.3-p3 hotfix: fixed a syntax error introduced by v1.0.3-p2's
        landscape review refactor — the if/else split for landscape/portrait
        move-list rendering forgot the closing `}` for the `if(reviewMode){`
        block, breaking the renderInternal() try/catch structure and causing
        a SyntaxError that made the entire chess.html script fail to parse
        (app showed a black screen on startup). Added the missing
        `} // close if(reviewMode)` after the move-list rendering branches.
      * v1.0.3-p4: landscape review layout — board+moves now FILL the full
        viewport width edge-to-edge. Removed the max-width cap on .review-moves
        (was calc(var(--rv-board-w) * 0.90)); move list now takes ALL remaining
        width via flex:1 1 0. .review-left padding changed from 2px 4px to 0
        so the board is flush with the screen's left edge. .review-moves
        padding tightened to 2px 2px 2px 4px so it's flush with the right
        edge. Board + moves together span 100% of viewport width with no
        gap between them. Board width cap changed from 65% to 55% of viewport
        width (move list gets ~45%). Move list scrolls vertically when
        content overflows (overflow-y:auto on .review-moves).
      * v1.0.3-p4: main-UI move-list scroll-position preservation. Before
        app.innerHTML=h, capture .mlist.scrollTop; after innerHTML replacement,
        restore it. This fixes the "move list keeps scrolling back to the top"
        bug caused by engine search triggering render() 10-50x/sec, each time
        rebuilding the DOM and resetting scrollTop to 0. Only runs in non-review
        mode (review mode has its own scrollIntoView logic).
      * v1.0.3-p5: landscape review layout — move list now has its OWN
        INDEPENDENT scroll viewport. .review-body changed from overflow-y:auto
        (whole-body scroll) to overflow:hidden (no body scroll). .review-top
        changed from flex:0 0 auto to flex:1 1 0 (fills all height above
        .review-bottom). .review-moves gets height:100% + min-height:0 so it
        fills the row height and scrolls internally via overflow-y:auto.
        .review-left gets height:100% + justify-content:center so the board is
        vertically centered in the row. The board stays fixed while only the
        move list scrolls. .review-bottom stays pinned at the bottom
        (flex:0 0 auto, no scroll).
      * v1.0.3-p5 audit fixes (first-principles code audit):
        - tablebase.js: removed a buggy regex that added an extra dot to move
          numbers (turned "1. e4" into "1.. e4"). The first regex already
          handles "1.e4" → "1. e4" and the third handles "1 e4" → "1. e4".
        - tablebase.js: removed dead `isCapture` computation in
          _executeAndRecord (was never read; move.enPassant is always undefined).
        - game-logic.js: queryECOBookMove now falls through to the level-1
          hash index when level-3 and level-2 both miss. Previously it degraded
          to a full ECO_OPENINGS scan, hurting ECO lookup performance for
          3+ move openings not in the level-3 index.
      * v1.0.3-p6: review move-list independent scroll — the REAL root cause
        was that scrollIntoView was called on EVERY render (10-50x/sec during
        engine analysis), yanking the move list back to the active move and
        preventing the user from scrolling independently. Now scrollIntoView
        only fires when reviewStep CHANGES (tracked via _lastReviewStepScrolled).
        Also removed the redundant setTimeout(50) scrollIntoView in reviewGoTo
        (renderInternal now handles it via the guard). enterReview resets
        _lastReviewStepScrolled to -2 so the first render after entering review
        mode scrolls the active move into view.
      * v1.0.3-p7: landscape review — TWO-LAYER SCROLL design. The body
        (.review-body) now scrolls vertically (overflow-y:auto, was overflow:
        hidden) so the user can scroll to see the chart, slider, eval bar, nav
        buttons, and analyze button when they don't all fit. The move list
        (.review-moves) keeps its OWN independent scroll viewport
        (overflow-y:auto with height = board height via --rv-board-h CSS var).
        Board sizing: board takes 60% of viewport width (ALWAYS > move-list
        width which gets 40%), NOT capped by REVIEW_CELL or viewport height.
        If the board is taller than the viewport, the user scrolls the body to
        see the board's bottom + chart + controls. Board + moves together fill
        100% of viewport width edge-to-edge, no gap. JS sets --rv-board-h CSS
        variable on .review-body so the move list height matches the board.
      * v1.0.3-p8: touch-slide on the review board now scrolls the whole
        review body. Two changes: (1) the global touchmove handler that
        preventDefault's board touches now SKIPS the preventDefault when
        reviewMode is true (so the browser's native scroll takes over);
        (2) the review board's .bgrid gets touch-action:pan-y (overriding the
        base .bgrid's touch-action:none) so vertical pans are handled by the
        browser as scroll. Horizontal pans are still blocked. Main-game mode
        is unaffected — board slides still don't scroll the page there.
      * v1.0.3-p9: review-body scroll preservation — capture
        .review-body.scrollTop before app.innerHTML=h and restore after,
        parallel to the v1.0.3-p4 .mlist preservation. Prevents the review
        body from yanking back to top on every render in landscape review mode.
      * v1.0.3-p9: move-list scroll isolation — replaced
        scrollIntoView({block:'center'}) (which scrolled ALL ancestors
        including .review-body) with a manual scrollTop computation on the
        move-list container only: _rList.scrollTop = _rAct.offsetTop -
        (_rList.clientHeight/2) + (_rAct.offsetHeight/2). This preserves the
        user's .review-body scroll position.
      * v1.0.3-p9 audit fixes: onBestMove staleness check moved before safety
        timer clear (ai-bridge.js — prevents doAIMove hang on stale bestmove);
        brace-comment loop iteration cap (tablebase.js — prevents infinite loop
        on unmatched `{`); stale comment cleanup (ui.js, index.html.tpl).
      * v1.0.3-p10: review nav buttons stretch full width in ALL orientations —
        promoted .review-nav and .review-nav .btn CSS from the landscape media
        query to base CSS (outside media queries). Nav buttons now fill the
        full row width in both portrait and landscape.
      * v1.0.3-p10: move-list scroll-to-active logic unified for both
        orientations — replaced single offsetTop read with a DOM walk that
        accumulates offsetTop from the active element up to the scroll
        container. Works correctly regardless of which element is the
        offsetParent (which differs between portrait and landscape layouts).
      * v1.0.3-p12: portrait chart width cap removed — was capped at
        min(viewportW-48, 400)-12 (max ~352px); now uses viewportW-12 for
        both orientations (unified with landscape).
      * v1.0.3-p11: eval trend chart SVG left/right padding reduced from
        36px to 8px — chart points and lines fully utilize horizontal space.
      * v1.0.3-p11: portrait move-list scroll root cause fix — the p10
        offsetParent walk failed in portrait because .review-moves has
        position:static, so .rmv-block's offsetParent jumped to
        .review-overlay (position:fixed), skipping the container. Replaced
        with getBoundingClientRect(): _offsetTop = _rActRect.top -
        _rListRect.top + _rList.scrollTop. Works in both orientations.
  - index.html.tpl (AGPL v3):
      * Landscape review CSS: complete redesign (see ui.js changes above).
        New classes: .review-top, .review-bottom, .review-nav.
        v1.0.3-p7: .review-body is overflow-y:auto (TWO-LAYER SCROLL — body
        scrolls to reveal chart/buttons). .review-top is flex:0 0 auto (height
        = board height, intrinsic). .review-moves has height:var(--rv-board-h)
        + min-height:0 + overflow-y:auto (INDEPENDENT scroll viewport matching
        board height). .review-bottom is flex:0 0 auto (pinned, visible via
        body scroll).
      * Removed the old per-size review overrides in compact/standard/
        tablet/large-tablet media queries (the new layout works at any
        size without per-size tweaks; only font sizes need adjustment
        on tall tablets, which remains).

The combined output (chess.html) is a combined work. The GPL v3 JavaScript
modules and AGPL v3 template retain their respective licenses. Since AGPL v3
imposes stricter requirements, its obligations effectively cover the entire
combined output.

